[normal]About Arqiva[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Arqiva is a media infrastructure and technology company operating at the heart of the broadcast and mobile communications industry and at the forefr
[normal]ont of network solutions and services in an increasingly digital world.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] Arqiva provides much of the infrastructure behind television, radio and wireless communications in the 
[normal]UK
[normal] and has a growing presence in 
[normal]Ireland
[normal], mainland Europe and the 
[normal]USA
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Arqiva w
[normal]as responsible for 
[normal]UK Digital ‘Switch-Over’ 
[normal]– engineering 
[normal]from analogue television to Freeview – a huge l
[normal]ogistical exercise which touched
[normal] every Parliamentary constituency, requiring an investment by
[normal] Arqiva of some £630m and was 
[normal]succes
[normal]sfully 
[normal]delivered to ti
[normal]me and budget.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Arqiva is also a founder member and shareholder of Freeview (Arqiva broadcasts all six Freeview multiplexes and is the licensed operator of two of them) and was a key launch technology partner for Freesat. Arqiva is also the licensed operat
[normal]or of the Digital One national commercial DAB digital radio multiplex.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Arqiva operates
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]five international satellite teleports, over 70 other staffed locations, and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]thousands of shared radio sites throughout the 
[normal]UK
[normal] and 
[normal]Ireland
[normal] including masts, towers and r
[normal]ooftops from under 30 to over 300 metres tall.
